<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
<script>
$(document).ready(function(){

  $("#searchForm").submit(function(e){
    e.preventDefault();
    let dest = $("#dest").val();
    let date = $("#date").val();
    if(dest=="" || date==""){
      alert("Please fill all fields!");
      return;
    }
    $('html, body').animate({
      scrollTop: $("#destinations").offset().top
    }, 500);
  });

  $(".bookBtn").click(function(){
    let place = $(this).closest(".card").find("h5").text();
    $("#modalInfo").html("You are booking a trip to <b>" + place + "</b>.");
    $("#bookModal").modal("show");
  });
});
</script>

</body>
</html>

Explanation:

HTML5: Used form inputs with `autocomplete`, `date`, and `range` types for selecting destinations, travel dates, and budget.
CSS3: Added positioning, box shadow, and hover effects to highlight destination cards.
JavaScript & DOM: Dynamically validates form and updates booking modal details.
jQuery: Used for smooth scrolling and modal interactions (`animate()`, `click()`).
Bootstrap: Used responsive grid system, buttons, badges, and modal for booking confirmation.
Responsive Design: Media query ensures layout adjusts for mobile and desktop screens for good usability.
